    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-06-10T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-06-10T00:00:00-05:00" n="261"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d261">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/2031</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Vladivostok</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_CJK1"
                        type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caldwell</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Vladivostok</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-06-10">
                            <hi rend="italic">June 10, 1918</hi>
                        </date>. <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received June 15, 6.40
                        p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Following telegram received to-day from <persName corresp="#p_HEL1"
                        >Harris</persName>, Irkutsk: <quote rend="blockquote">
                        <p>21, 10th. Courier from west reports real reason Czech trouble is
                            detention in Russia of all Czech troops by order of <persName
                                corresp="#p_TLDB1">Trotsky</persName>. Czechs in Siberia permitted
                            move forward while their comrades in Russia are detained. Mariinsk and
                            Novo Nikolaevsk still held by Czechs. Czech troops in Russia 38,000 and
                            in Siberia west of Irkutsk nearly 7,000. Temporary neutral zone made
                            between Irkutsk White Army west of city and of Red Army near
                            Nizhneudinsk. Inform Ambassador of above. Have not been able communicate
                            with Ambassador for fortnight.</p>
                    </quote>
                </p>
                <p>Peking informed.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_CJK1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Caldwell</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
